us divide. The results have implications not just for peacemaking in Northern Ireland, but for other societies emerging from conflict. The main lesson of peacemaking in Northern Ireland is that political reform has to be accompanied by social change across the society as a whole. Peace after conflict needs social as well as political change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholicszNorthern IrelandxAttitudes. 0aPeace-buildingzNorthern IrelandxHistoryy20th century. 0aPeace-buildingzNorthern IrelandxHistoryy21st century. 0aProtestantszNorthern IrelandxAttitudes. 0aPublic opinionzNorthern IrelandxHistoryy20th century. 0aPublic opinionzNorthern IrelandxHistoryy21st century. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2018. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh  a1998 Belfast Agreement.  aCatholics.  aNorthern Ireland.  acommunity autonomy.  aconflict transformation.  aconstitutional position.  aeducation.  aethnonationalism.  apeace.  aperpetrators.  apolitical violence.  apolitics.  apost-conflict societies.  aprotestants.  apublic opinion.  areligion.  asocial change.  asocial cohesion.  atheory of consociationalism.  avictimhood.1 aHayes, Bernadette C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcAllister, Ian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMcAllister, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978071909903840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780719099038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780719099038/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyte